reased\" --> PartialCommit[Commit partial coverage<br/>advance class_checkpoint]\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:184:  itself fails — coverage data is the deciding signal.\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:191:A missing or unparsable `dynamic-access-coverage.json` after the initial\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:198:After every per-class iteration that committed a coverage gain — i.e. the\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:239:2. The dynamic-access coverage report is regenerated **after** the gate so\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:243:   Native Image must always work; partial dynamic-access coverage with a\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:260:    Improved -- no --> Keep{keep-tests-without-dynamic-access<br/>AND tests changed since start<br/>AND prompt_iterations > 0}\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:308:The `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` flag is the only mechanism for\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:309:producing a successful run when no class achieved coverage gain. It is\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:320:| `utility_scripts/dynamic_access_report.py` | `load_dynamic_access_coverage_report`, `compute_class_delta`, `format_call_sites`. |\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:322:| `utility_scripts/native_test_verification.py` | `verify_native_test_passes` — the native-test gate invoked for each configured batch of classes with coverage gain; it runs JVM-agent metadata first, native tracing only as fallback, and Codex last. See [native-test-verification.md](native-test-verification.md). |\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:323:| `prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md` | Per-class prompt template. |\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:331:1. The dynamic-access report at the end of Phase 2 contains zero uncovered\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:334:   `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` was set and tests changed.\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:341:   coverage gain (Resolved or PartialCommit), and once more for any final\nforge/schemas/benchmark_run_metrics_schema.json:12:        \"coverageRatio\"\nforge/schemas/benchmark_run_metrics_schema.json:23:        \"coverageRatio\": {\nforge/schemas/benchmark_run_metrics_schema.json:83:            \"coverageRatio\",\nforge/schemas/benchmark_run_metrics_schema.json:95:            \"coverageRatio\": {\nforge/schemas/benchmark_run_metrics_schema.json:135:        \"code_coverage_percent\",\nforge/schemas/benchmark_run_metrics_schema.json:175:        \"code_coverage_percent\": {\nforge/schemas/benchmark_run_metrics_schema.json:294:        \"code_coverage_percent\",\nforge/schemas/benchmark_run_metrics_schema.json:348:        \"code_coverage_percent\": {\nforge/schemas/benchmark_run_metrics_schema.json:427:              \"code_coverage_percent\": 10.9,\nforge/schemas/strategy_schema.json:41:        \"description\": \"Primary workflow to run first in composite strategies (e.g., increase_dynamic_access_coverage).\"\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:22:| **Repository automation (Metadata Forge)** | Generate or repair metadata using LLM-driven pipelines. | Per coordinate, the toolkit can: (1) **add support for a new library** — generate a JUnit / Kotlin / Scala test suite, scaffold metadata, and iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access is collected ([`add_new_library_support.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py)); (2) **fix a Java compilation (`javac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` mirror of per-version metrics (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:55:- Coverage collection (JaCoCo) and dynamic-access reporting per coordinate.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:63:- Schedule-driven: full metadata sweep every three days to prevent incomplete or breaking metadata from shipping in releases, new-library-version compatibility (every six hours), Docker image vulnerability scans, scheduled release every two weeks, scheduled coverage publication.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:73:`publish-scheduled-coverage.yml` derives, from committed `stats/` and `metadata/**/index.json`:\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:74:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:75:- `COVERAGE.md` — the per-library coverage table linked from the README. Each\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:77:  `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/index.json` file and the dynamic-access coverage\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:83:sync with the generated coverage table through the bulk-update PRs created by\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:85:badge, graph, and history artifacts are published to the `stats/coverage` branch.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:90:1. **Add new library support** — generate a JUnit test suite, scaffold metadata, iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access metadata is collected.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:93:4. **Improve coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered dynamic-access call sites.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:104:| `library-update-request` | Issue / PR | Request or PR to improve support for an already-covered library, including coverage-improvement work. |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:223:- **FR-T-7** Dynamic-access coverage between consecutive tested versions of a library must not regress (enforced by reviewer skills `review-fixes-javac-fail`, `review-fixes-native-image-run-fail`, `review-fixes-java-run-fail`).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:263:- **NFR-7 Auditability.** Every Forge run produces a schema-validated metrics record; every coverage publish writes to a force-pushed branch with retained history.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:278:- Mirrored stats under `stats/`, a generated root `COVERAGE.md`, and aggregated coverage artifacts on `stats/coverage`.\n./docs/CI.md:46:- [.github/workflows/publish-scheduled-coverage.yml](../.github/workflows/publish-scheduled-coverage.yml): scheduled/manual workflow that generates repository coverage badges and the coverage dashboard from exploded stats files under [stats/](../stats/) and repository [metadata/**/index.json](../metadata/), then force-pushes the published artifacts to the `stats/coverage` branch. The published branch only keeps `COVERAGE.md`, `latest/badges.json`, `latest/metrics-over-time.svg`, `latest/metrics-over-time-dark.svg`, and `history/history.json`.\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:29:To run the same coverage with future defaults enabled:\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:145:Generate coverage for the library under test exercised by our tests. Report contains coverage that focus exclusively on the provided library JARs, excluding unrelated external dependencies.\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:318:- Generate dynamic access coverage report: `./gradlew generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:319:  Output: `metadata