e of already-supported libraries.\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:53:| **Dynamic-access report** | JSON written by Gradle task `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` to `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`, listing classes and per-class call sites that require dynamic-access metadata, marked covered/uncovered. |\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:83:- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` — only honored by dynamic-access\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:84:  strategies; see [dynamic-access-workflow.md](dynamic-access-workflow.md).\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:96:  `dynamic-access-iteration`).\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:131:  testing, dynamic-access reporting, native metadata exploration, metadata\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:214:For dynamic-access workflows, Forge passes the issue number and configured\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:216:dynamic-access report exceeds a configured class or call chunk limit, the\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:227:- [Dynamic access workflow](dynamic-access-workflow.md) — guided test\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:228:  generation driven by the dynamic-access coverage report.\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:237:  final recovery to Codex. Used as the per-class gate in the dynamic-access\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:243:- [Coverage improvement workflow](improve-library-coverage.md) — generates\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:244:  additional tests to improve dynamic-access coverage on an existing library\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:8:These PRs are created by the scheduled compatibility workflow and are expected to update supported library versions by changing `metadata/**/index.json`. They may also refresh the generated root `COVERAGE.md` when tested-version changes affect the coverage table.\n./stats/com.aayushatharva.brotli4j/brotli4j/1.18.0/stats.json:7:          \"coverageRatio\" : 1.0,\n./stats/com.aayushatharva.brotli4j/brotli4j/1.18.0/stats.json:12:      \"coverageRatio\" : 1.0,\n./stats/com.aayushatharva.brotli4j/brotli4j/1.18.0/execution-metrics.json:16:            \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n./stats/com.aayushatharva.brotli4j/brotli4j/1.18.0/execution-metrics.json:21:        \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n./stats/com.aayushatharva.brotli4j/brotli4j/1.18.0/execution-metrics.json:55:      \"code_coverage_percent\": 4.01\n./stats/com.aayushatharva.brotli4j/service/1.18.0/stats.json:6:      \"coverageRatio\" : 1.0,\n./stats/com.aayushatharva.brotli4j/service/1.18.0/execution-metrics.json:15:        \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n./stats/com.aayushatharva.brotli4j/service/1.18.0/execution-metrics.json:29:      \"code_coverage_percent\": 100.0\n./stats/biz.aQute.bnd/biz.aQute.bnd.util/6.4.1/stats.json:7:          \"coverageRatio\" : 1.0,\n./stats/biz.aQute.bnd/biz.aQute.bnd.util/6.4.1/stats.json:12:      \"coverageRatio\" : 1.0,\n./stats/biz.aQute.bnd/biz.aQute.bnd.util/6.4.1/execution-metrics.json:16:            \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n./stats/biz.aQute.bnd/biz.aQute.bnd.util/6.4.1/execution-metrics.json:21:        \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n./stats/biz.aQute.bnd/biz.aQute.bnd.util/6.4.1/execution-metrics.json:55:      \"code_coverage_percent\": 3.16\n./forge/docs/native-metadata-exploration.md:41:> [Dynamic-access workflow](dynamic-access-workflow.md) ·\n./forge/docs/native-metadata-exploration.md:143:where `<class-key>` is a sanitized form of the dynamic-access class the\n./forge/docs/native-metadata-exploration.md:404:| Dynamic-access workflow | [dynamic-access-workflow.md](dynamic-access-workflow.md) |\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-java-run-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR described as `fixes-java-run-fail` or one that fixes Java/JVM runtime test failures for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the Java runtime fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair tests, dependencies, or narrow runtime setup after an existing library version compiles, but the JVM-based test fails when it runs. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library already exists, so the goal is to restore Java runtime behavior for the new version while preserving meaningful test and dynamic-access coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:17:- Be more relaxed than `library-new-request`: do not reject only because a test resembles older coverage, stays in an existing package layout, or contains compatibility branches for multiple supported versions.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:18:- Do not accept changes that remove meaningful test coverage just to make `java` pass.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:20:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:21:- For numeric gates, compare the reported evidence as-is. Do not inspect generation filters, agent configuration, or metadata contents to second-guess why dynamic-access or metadata-count numbers are what they are.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:56:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:59:   - Do not use `user-code-filter.json`, agent configuration, or metadata file contents to argue that the reported dynamic-access values are not comparable. Use the stats values as reported unless the stats are missing or stale.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:60:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:61:   - If `totalCalls` increases while `coveredCalls` stays flat or the ratio drops, ask for additional test coverage or metadata unless the uncovered calls are clearly outside the library behavior under test.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:69:   - Do not require an exact match. Differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:71:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/runtime-surface change.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:77:   - Prefer seeing the full target `test` lane green because a Java runtime fix can still reduce native-image coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:79:   - If CI is flaky but the diff and coverage comparison are sound, ask for a rerun instead of blocking on speculation.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:87:- Dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previous and new tested versions, or any apparent drop is convincingly explained by a changed upstream API/runtime surface.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:95:- Dynamic-access coverage drops without a credible explanation and replacement coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:103:- The API or runtime behavior change is plausible but the PR does not explain why a coverage drop is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:110:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:112:- For deleted or bypassed coverage: say that the PR fixes Java runtime execution by removing coverage and should instead adapt the test to the new runtime behavior.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:114:- For native skips that does not depend on the open-ended dynamic class loading: say that the PR avoids the failing native path instead of fixing it, so it does not demonstrate native-image runtime coverage.\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:9:  - `run(...)`: runs a single generation attempt. It generates the initial dynamic-access report, falls back to `BasicIterativeStrategy` only if no usable guidance exists at the start, otherwise enters the dynamic-access class iteration immediately and counts success only after metadata generation, retest, `generateLibraryStats`, and a commit for the library iteration succeed.\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:10:  - `__init__(...)`: keeps the dynamic strategy config minimal by requiring only the class-specific dynamic-access prompt and dynamic-access-specific iteration limits, while providing internal defaults for the start-of-run basic fallback prompts and fallback iteration limits.\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:11:  - `_run_dynamic_access_phase(...)`: uncovered-class iteration using coverage deltas from dynamic-access reports; initializes `exhausted_classes = set()` for the phase, emits targeted prompts per uncovered class, includes the current uncovered dynamic-access call-site list in every prompt, retries `./gradlew test` failures inside a bounded per-class mini-loop by sending the failing output back to the agent, clears agent context after each class attempt sequence, treats the phase as successful once any dynamic-access call site becomes covered, enforces per-class prompt-attempt limits, and fails the generation if the dynamic-access report disappears mid-phase.\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:12:  - `_generate_dynamic_access_report(...)`: runs `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` and loads parsed report data from `dynamic-access-coverage.json`.\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:17:  - `load_dynamic_access_coverage_report(...)`: parses JSON report payload into typed dataclasses.\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:53:    Strategy->>Report: `load_dynamic_access_coverage_report(...)`\n./stats/biz.aQute.bnd/biz.aQute.bnd.annotation/6.4.1/stats.json:7:          \"coverageRatio\" : 1.0,\n./stats/biz.aQute.bnd/biz.aQute.bnd.annotation/6.4.1/stats.json:12:      \"coverageRatio\" : 1.0,\n./forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:7:> **See also:** [Dynamic-access workflow](dynamic-access-workflow.md) ·\n./forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:48:The gate is the per-class success criterion for the dynamic-access workflow\n./forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:63:| Output directory | Caller | Absolute staging root for this gate invocation. The caller picks a path namespaced per (library, class) for the dynamic-access caller, or per coordinate for non-class-scoped callers — same convention as [native-metadata-exploration.md §4](native-metadata-exploration.md#4-output). The gate writes JVM-agent metadata to `<output_dir>/agent`, merged trace metadata to `<output_dir>/trace`, and writes durable repository metadata only after the final native-image-utils merge succeeds. |\n./forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:265:| `dynamic_access_iterative` per-class loop ([dynamic-access-workflow.md §6.2 / §6.4](dynamic-access-workflow.md)) | After every class with a coverage gain (Resolved or PartialCommit) | `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/build/natively-collected/<class-key>/` |\n./forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:268:The dynamic-access caller invokes the gate per class; the fix-native-run\n./stats/biz.aQute.bnd/biz.aQute.bnd.annotation/6.4.1/execution-metrics.json:16:  