e to prove that the submitted metadata is complete or necessary.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:23:- Treat `0/0` dynamic-access coverage as a valid no-calls case, not as failed coverage. Do not reject a PR only because the exploded stats report `0/0` dynamic-access calls while the PR adds metadata; those stats can miss metadata required through downstream libraries.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:24:- Do not explicitly read or review individual metadata entries. Use the metadata entry count reported in the PR description for the metadata/dynamic-access mismatch check; do not manually count entries from metadata files. When the PR reports both library metadata entries and test-only metadata entries, use their sum as the PR-reported metadata entry count. Only request investigation when the covered dynamic-access call count is at least 75% higher than that PR-reported total.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:57:   - For metadata/dynamic-access mismatch checks, use only the metadata entry count reported in the PR description, such as `Metadata entries`, or legacy fields such as `Entries` and `Entries found` in older PRs; add `Test-only metadata entries` when the PR reports it; do not manually count metadata entries from files.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:61:5. Compare the PR claims, test, and reported coverage as one unit.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:62:   - If the PR claims specific coverage numbers that do not line up with the diff, ask for investigation.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:63:   - Confirm reported dynamic-access coverage is above 20% when the stats include dynamic-access calls.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:64:   - If the PR reports zero dynamic-access calls and `reachability-metadata.json` is `{}`, that is acceptable as long as the test is library-specific and the scope is otherwise correct.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:65:   - If the PR reports zero dynamic-access calls while adding metadata, do not reject it on that basis alone; dynamic-access stats can miss metadata required through downstream libraries.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:66:   - If the stats report 20% coverage or lower for non-zero dynamic-access calls, or no usable coverage signal for claimed dynamic-access behavior, ask for stronger tests or refreshed coverage evidence.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:67:   - Ask for metadata/coverage mismatch investigation only when the covered dynamic-access call count is at least 75% higher than the PR-reported metadata entry count, where the reported count is `Metadata entries` plus `Test-only metadata entries` when both are present. For older PRs, use legacy `Entries` or `Entries found` as the metadata entry count.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:90:  - Reported dynamic-access coverage is 20% or lower for non-zero dynamic-access calls, absent for claimed dynamic-access behavior, or not credible from the diff.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:97:- For native skips that does not depend on the open-ended dynamic class loading: say that the PR avoids the failing native path instead of fixing it, so it does not demonstrate native-image runtime coverage.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:101:- For insufficient dynamic-access coverage: say that new-library PRs need dynamic-access coverage above 20% when there are dynamic-access calls to cover, and ask for stronger tests or refreshed coverage evidence.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:102:- For unsupported coverage claims: ask for refreshed coverage evidence when the PR makes concrete coverage claims that are not supported by the diff.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:103:- For metadata/dynamic-access entry mismatch: ask for investigation only when covered dynamic-access calls are at least 75% higher than the PR-reported metadata entry count, summin